Scottish independent schools maintain a curriculum of academic excellence and this continued in 2018 with another series of outstanding exam results, bolstered by individual and collective success in sport, the arts, music and other collective endeavours.
With over 30,000 pupils across Scotland, these schools, represented by The Scottish Council of Independent Schools (SCIS), aim to provide the best possible level of service to their pupils and their parents.
Independent schools aim to prepare students for further higher education, their chosen careers and their place in the world as global citizens.
As an area of education able to develop and adopt a personalised school curriculum, we see that modern languages continue to be a popular and in-demand subject in schools.
Nelson Mandela said: "If you speak to a man in a language he understands, the message will reach his brain.
